To all people that speakes of an outvvard baptisme; dippers, sprinklers, and others Also the errors answered, holden forth by Thomas Larkham, called by the world a minister, at VVe[x]ford he was then with a reproofe to the offenders; and also some queries to all people to be read within that yee may all know that, that which may bee knowne of God is manifest within; Rom: 1: 19... From a friend to all that breath after jesus; known to the world by the name Humphry Norton; though amongst the scorners called a Qvaker. Norton, Humphrey, fl. 1655-1659.
16 p.
s.n., [London? : 1659]
Caption title. Imprint from Wing. Gathered in 2's. P. 9 misnumbered p. 8. Reproduction of the original in the Friends' House Library, London.
